1
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:04,155
-Last season on The O.C.:
-Theresa's pregnant.

2
00:00:04,320 --> 00:00:05,878
-You don't have to leave.
-Then come with me.

3
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:08,315
I'm leaving.
I can't let Theresa do this by herself.

4
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:09,879
Oh, my God! It's a palace.

5
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:12,679
Look, you're getting what you wanted.
I'm moving in with you.

6
00:00:12,840 --> 00:00:14,751
-You going somewhere?
-Like, say, San Quentin.

7
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:16,911
-Thank you.
-Could we convince you to stay?

8
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:20,072
He's the first real friend I've ever had.
He's the only real friend I've ever had.

9
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:23,312
I understand why you have to do this,
but I wish you didn't have to.

10
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:26,870
Before he got here, I was the biggest
loser. This place was hell for me.

11
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:29,918
I can't even imagine what
it's gonna be like here without him.

12
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:42,510
So we've knocked down
the retaining wall...

13
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:45,274
-...to allow for more flow.
-Great. When do you think...

14
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:47,237
...we will have achieved flow?

15
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:49,516
When will we be done
tearing your house apart?

16
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:51,033
No, my house is torn apart.

17
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:54,317
The construction's got nothing
to do with it. Ballpark, Archie.

18
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:58,519
It's September now. I'd say two weeks.
A month tops.

19
00:00:58,760 --> 00:01:01,558
-Six weeks.
-Well, in the meantime--

20
00:01:04,880 --> 00:01:07,189
In the meantime,
could you please try to convince...

21
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:09,749
...the fellas here to wear something
in a shirt?

22
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:12,878
My neighbors have started to refer
to my home as "the manhole. "

23
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,792
-T oo Village People?
-Exactly.

24
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:16,917
-I'll talk to my guys.
-Hey, Archie.

25
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:18,911
Sandy.

26
00:01:22,840 --> 00:01:26,833
And don't ever get married.
And if you do, don't ever have kids.

27
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:31,399
Well, good news. Archie thinks
the remodel should be done...

28
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:34,836
...anytime between now and....
Well, he didn't say never...

29
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,594
...but there was subtext.
I'd love some coffee.

30
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:42,916
Thank you.
Boy, am I excited to head into court...

31
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:45,514
...for day one of this riveting
nuisance lawsuit...

32
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:48,513
...where one yacht owner
feels that this other yacht owner...

33
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:52,036
...is in violation of the noise ordinance
at Crystal Cove.

34
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:57,474
Butterscotch donkey, El Paso, lampshade,
truck stop, stethoscope--

35
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:59,835
I know you think
that l' m ignoring you...

36
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,436
...so you speak in gibberish
to see if I'm listening.

37
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:06,034
-You were listening.
-Nope.

38
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,875
I'm distracted by today's paper.
Actually, the date of today's paper.

39
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:12,793
-He's gonna come back.
-By the time school starts...

40
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:15,997
...or by the time Archie
finishes the remodel?

41
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:18,958
What do you want me to do?
Tie him up, stuff him in a trunk?

42
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,395
At this point? Y es.

43
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,515
I have had enough of your hippie
parenting psychobabble.

44
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,114
So that's the problem.

45
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:29,430
It's not just smothering
overprotectiveness...

46
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:32,034
...that kept him from having a friend
until Ryan came.

47
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:34,953
Sometimes the best thing for a kid
is to have some space.

48
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:38,158
The Pacific Ocean?
That's not enough space?

49
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,999
If you force him to return,
he'll wanna run away again.

50
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,512
I don't care what he wants.

51
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:45,796
I don't care what he thinks is fair.

52
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:49,032
-He could have died out there.
-Okay, so you can blame me.

53
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:52,636
And he can blame us. And we can keep
passing the buck all summer long.

54
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,268
Summer is over. School is starting.

55
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:56,998
This is where he belongs.

56
00:02:57,160 --> 00:03:00,516
-He's gonna figure that out.
-I'm tired of waiting for that.

57
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,512
Bring him home, Sandy.

58
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,159
Bring him home.

59
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,518
Could it be any hotter?

60
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,477
I feel like my flesh is melting.

61
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:55,995
I just hope it melts evenly.

62
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:04,349
Damn, girl. Break me off a piece of that.

63
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,716
He's totally checking you out.

64
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:16,834
So my mom's trying to drag me
to Cardio Barre again.

65
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,831
It's her idea
of mother-daughter bonding.

66
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,116
-Cardio Barre?
-She says it's the new Tae Bo...

67
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:25,068
-...so maybe I can learn to kick her ass.
-I don't think you need any more cardio.

68
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,876
-What's that supposed to mean?
-Nothing.

69
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:32,272
It's just that-- Well, and I mean this
in the least scandalous way...

70
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:34,874
...but you're looking a little thin.

71
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:37,076
-I eat.
-Okay.

72
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,800
Oh, God. You definitely drink.

73
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:44,235
What's in this, lighter fluid?

74
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,636
This is a Newport Beach lced Tea.

75
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,394
This is 1 0:00 in the morning.
It's a little early.

76
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:51,153
For who?

77
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:58,392
This bikini is so uncomfortable.
I need to go get a new one.

78
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,312
-You wanna go to South Coast?
-Totally.

79
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:03,392
-There's a Paul Frank sale Wednesday.
-Wednesday? I can't.

80
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,199
-I have plans with Zach.
-More plans with Zach, huh?

81
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:10,512
Yes. The more time I spend with Zach,
the less time I have to think about....

82
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:14,150
God, what's-his-face.
Built like a beanpole, curly hair.

83
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:18,233
Runs away on a sailboat, leaving nothing
but a note for his girlfriend who cried...

84
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:22,757
...until July Fourth when she decided
she doesn't cry over bitches on boats.

85
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,354
Seth.

86
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,477
His name, it's Seth.

87
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:30,154
I know. I'm doing that thing
where I pretend I don't...

88
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:34,871
...and I have to use a lot of descriptive
insults to give voice to my inner pain.

89
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:40,673
So yeah, can't do it Wednesday.

90
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,114
More plans with Zach.

91
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:46,273
Well, it's a formality, really.
I refuse to get close to him.

92
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:48,829
I will never be close to a boy again.

93
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,590
Yeah, I know what you mean.

94
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,713
That's good.
All right, thanks for the ride.

95
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,711
Don't forget your lunch.

96
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:12,191
I peeled your orange for you.

97
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,673
Thanks, but it's probably not
the best way to fit in with these guys.

98
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:18,159
Right.

99
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,072
All right, well, I'll--

100
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:26,435
Yeah, you don't want
the foreman to get angry.

101
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,875
He's always angry. He's an angry man.

102
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:34,150
Maybe tonight we could rent a movie
or play pool or something.

103
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:35,958
Yeah. Pool sounds good.

104
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,799
See you.

105
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:51,910
Honey, I've got to pick up Kaitlin
from junior lifeguards.

106
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:55,117
Maybe she can save her sister
from drowning in self-pity.

107
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:58,477
What is that flower truck doing
in our driveway? I get the feeling...

108
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:01,438
-...that it's been there every week.
-Because it has.

109
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:04,840
We get flowers delivered every week?

110
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,150
Yes, Cal. They're living things.
They die.

111
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:13,875
Do you hear clicking on the phone? Every
time I dial out, I swear I hear a clicking.

112
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:16,270
Okay, Nixon. Paranoid much?

113
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:20,119
What's going on with you?
You're either hopped up on blow...

114
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:22,953
-...or something is seriously wrong.
-It's nothing.

115
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,792
It's my blood-thinning medication.

116
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:28,794
-Sometimes it makes me feel--
-Wacko? Like all summer long?

117
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,391
I'm taking Kaitlin
to go look at new ponies.

118
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:35,437
What's wrong with China?

119
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,149
China has alopecia.

120
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:42,592
I was hoping that the hair treatments
would work, but bald as a baby's ass.

121
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:45,877
It's just not right for a little girl
to love a hairless pony.

122
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:48,395
-I suppose that's fair.
-Thanks.

123
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:52,438
You're not charging that
on the company card, are you?

124
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,839
Why?

125
00:07:57,200 --> 00:08:01,273
Because we can't claim Kaitlin's
new pony as a business expense.

126
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,510
-It's illegal.
-Oh, I know.

127
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,750
I was gonna put it on the black card.

128
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,512
Bye, sweetie.

129
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:16,870
Yeah, they're all done there.

130
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:37,477
-Hello?
-Luke, it's Kirsten.

131
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:40,279
Hey, Mrs. Cohen. How you doing?

132
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:42,749
Although I think I can answer that one
for myself.

133
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,389
Yeah. Is he there?

134
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,433
It's for you.

135
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:51,590
-Hello?
-Seth. It's Mom.

136
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:53,432
Mom.

137
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:56,160
Blond, sharp Anglican features,
cute little nose?

138
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,439
Come home.

139
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,319
-Did Ryan come back?
-Seth Ezekiel--

140
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:04,074
Using the dreaded middle name
won't help to forge a bond.

141
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,753
This has gone on long enough.

142
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:09,597
Not yet. I signed up to teach
more sailing lessons through September.

143
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:11,955
-Portland needs me, Mother.
-So do l.

144
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,997
Here's the thing, though.

145
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,720
I hate it there. I'm never coming back
to Orange County.

146
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:21,395
If you and Dad want to move to,
say, anywhere else on the planet...

147
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,949
-...then we can talk.
-Here I was, crazy to think...

148
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:27,510
...that a simple appeal from a mother
to a son might get some traction.

149
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,796
Yeah, well, that is crazy. Bye.

150
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:32,190
So you're just gonna hang up on--?

151
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:43,390
-Gave in and called him, huh?
-He used to be such a sweet kid.

152
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:46,279
And he's turning out to be
quite the angry young man.

153
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:48,431
I had the same talk with him
this afternoon.

154
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:53,310
Doesn't he know that we didn't want
Ryan to leave any more than he did?

155
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:57,598
Well, right now it's--
It's not about what he knows.

156
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,830
It's about how he feels.

157
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:05,151
This house just seems so empty.

158
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:08,392
We're gonna have to rip up this floor
a little bit. Is that okay?

159
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,353
And yet so full.

160
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:14,153
Full of sweaty, shirtless men.

161
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:16,356
You'd think you'd be in heaven.

162
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:20,639
That's Jimmy.
I said we'd have dinner with him, but....

163
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,593
I'll talk to him.

164
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:26,318
Jimbo. How goes it?

165
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:29,392
It goes fantastic. You guys
still gonna join me and Hailey...

166
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:31,232
-...on the boat for dinner?
-No.

167
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,595
Kirsten's not feeling so great.

168
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,673
-Seth still won't come home, huh?
-No, he'll come home.

169
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:39,115
You know, he's got no real choice.

170
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:42,829
I'm just trying to figure out the best way
for him to realize that.

171
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:48,310
Well, if you're too tough on him, and you
bring him back kicking and screaming....

172
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,879
It'll only make things worse.

173
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:54,272
The last thing anybody wants is a bitter,
resentful teenager in the house.

174
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:58,077
He won't talk to me.
He won't talk to Kirsten.

175
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:01,118
Well, maybe there's somebody else
he'll talk to.

176
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:12,157
I wanted to ensure you weren't slacking
or trying to punch out early.

177
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:14,880
-I wish. How are you?
-Pretty good.

178
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,792
-You?
-That was real nice of Kirsten...

179
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:19,520
-...to send those baby clothes.
-Kirsten loves to shop.

180
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:22,069
-Even for the unborn.
-How's the remodel going?

181
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:25,228
A lot like this. A disaster.

182
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:29,632
-As long as it keeps her distracted, right?
-It's not really doing the trick anymore.

183
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,473
-Seth wants to stay in Portland?
-School is approaching...

184
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:37,155
...and everybody's digging in their heels,
holding their positions.

185
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,754
-So you going up there?
-Y eah, I've always liked Luke.

186
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:43,390
He's like a big golden retriever.

187
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,236
Actually, he kind of is.

188
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:49,158
You wanna come?

189
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:51,949
A one-two punch
might be more effective.

190
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,917
You and me...

191
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,991
...unbeatable combination.

192
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,671
He was pretty mad at me last time
I saw him.

193
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:01,513
-We haven't talked since.
-He's pretty mad at everybody.

194
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:04,672
I don't know.
Theresa's got some tests. I got work.

195
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:06,159
Well....

196
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:12,196
Just in case. Don't worry
if you don't use it. I got a great fare.

197
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:22,399
Good luck.

198
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,712
Take care, kid.

199
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,917
Breakfast is ready. My mom left early.

200
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:57,071
-There's plenty of food.
-Thanks.

201
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:01,159
-What's that?
-Nothing.

202
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:04,437
Sandy needed some help
convincing Seth to come home.

203
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:06,113
Is that why he came by yesterday?

204
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:08,350
-He said he was just checking in.
-Y eah.

205
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:11,159
No. I don't know.
I mean, Seth's still angry.

206
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,959
-I guess he blames his parents.
-For you leaving?

207
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,879
Yeah.

208
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:19,114
I can't imagine what he thinks about me.

209
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:22,031
So are you gonna go to Portland?

210
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,713
No, I can't.

211
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:27,276
-You should go if you wanna go.
-It's for them to figure out as a family.

212
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:30,359
-You're not part of their family?
-Not anymore.

213
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:32,272
I should get to work.

214
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:47,954
Hey, Cal.

215
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:52,272
Always a pleasure. Although, if I may,
why are we meeting in a parking garage?

216
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,431
Because my office might be bugged.

217
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:57,114
My home, your home.
Who knows what the feds are up to?

218
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:59,669
Wow, you've really flipped your noodle,
haven't you?

219
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:02,035
Hey, I could be wearing a wire.

220
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,430
You never know.
Sure you don't wanna frisk me?

221
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:07,797
-I don't have time for jokes.
-Nor do l. I gotta be at the airport...

222
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:09,234
...in half an hour.

223
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,356
-I'm heading up to Portland.
-To see Seth?

224
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:12,999
-Yeah.
-I don't get it.

225
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:17,916
His best friend leaves, so he runs off
with another boy and his gay dad.

226
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:20,230
You gotta admit
it sounds kind of strange.

227
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,231
This from a guy
who is one klick away...

228
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,356
...from wearing a wig
and a fake mustache.

229
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:28,548
-You think my paranoia is unfounded.
-It's entertaining, but entirely unfounded.

230
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:31,518
I haven't heard anything
from my friends at the DA's office.

231
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:35,070
That doesn't make sense. DA comes
to see me at the beginning of summer...

232
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:38,630
