466
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:03,234
Give her some semblance
of a normal family dynamic.

467
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:07,029
Maybe Sunday dinners
you can come over here with....

468
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:09,475
-Hailey?
-Right, right.

469
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:13,079
-You two are still...?
-Yeah, we're great. She's fantastic.

470
00:32:13,240 --> 00:32:15,629
Sweet. Limber.

471
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:18,837
-How about you and Caleb?
-Not so limber.

472
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:26,958
I'll help. The best I can. Okay?

473
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:31,557
Thank you. And for the record,
I am happy for you.

474
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:37,159
For the record, I don't believe you,
but for Marissa's sake, I'll pretend to.

475
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:48,276
I can't believe you talked to the DA's
office yesterday and to me only now.

476
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:50,476
I was trying to bring
your grandson home.

477
00:32:50,640 --> 00:32:54,110
-He's staying. Thanks for asking.
-He's staying?

478
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:57,475
Want me to talk to him?
I can be quite persuasive.

479
00:32:57,640 --> 00:33:00,757
You better rest up. And stockpile
some of that persuasiveness.

480
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:02,990
Why? What did the DA say?

481
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:06,630
The clouds have gathered, Cal.
It's about to rain down on you.

482
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:10,759
On all of us. So put your storm
windows in, if you know what I mean.

483
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:12,797
-That bad, huh?
-Get your house in order.

484
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:16,669
The Newport Group. The family.
Do it soon.

485
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:22,759
Come on, Chino. Try and hurt me.

486
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:24,638
Make me feel pain.

487
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:26,995
-Wound me.
-Think of all the money Luke saves...

488
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:30,755
-...on therapy playing these games.
-I think he should still consider therapy.

489
00:33:30,920 --> 00:33:32,194
You're gonna pay for that.

490
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:34,510
Ryan. Telephone.

491
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:37,275
-Good luck.
-I'll wait here.

492
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:40,475
Okay. Here we go.

493
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,993
-Hello.
-Ryan?

494
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:43,832
Hi. What's wrong?

495
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:47,953
I went to the doctor's for the checkup.

496
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:52,069
And they couldn't find a heartbeat.

497
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:56,794
I lost the baby, Ryan. I guess in the first
couple months this can happen.

498
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:59,633
Okay. Okay, I'm coming back.

499
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:02,553
-I'm getting on the next flight, and....
-No.

500
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:04,791
-What?
-I think...

501
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:07,349
...that maybe we should see this
as a sign.

502
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:10,675
You know, I think it's a sign.

503
00:34:12,040 --> 00:34:14,600
Ryan, you're not happy with me.

504
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:17,316
You haven't been happy.

505
00:34:17,520 --> 00:34:20,751
The only reason you've stayed
is because of this baby.

506
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:23,437
And now there isn't a baby.

507
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:26,513
You don't want me to come home.

508
00:34:29,640 --> 00:34:31,790
You don't wanna come home.

509
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:38,869
Is this your battleground? Is this your...?

510
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:40,917
Hey, everything all right?

511
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:45,634
Theresa lost the baby.

512
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:34,037
Did you tell him?

513
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:39,717
Did he believe you?

514
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:43,031
Yeah, I think so.

515
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:53,630
It's for the best.
For you and him and for the baby.

516
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:08,791
What time's your cab get here?

517
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:10,918
Any minute.

518
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:15,234
-What are you gonna do now?
-I don't know.

519
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:19,359
Get my stuff out of Theresa's,
and then I'm homeless again.

520
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:22,314
Have I sold you
on the wonders of Portland?

521
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:24,072
We could take our show on the road.

522
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:28,678
I can't impose. Besides, I got this job.
It pays pretty well, so....

523
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,432
I'll figure something out.

524
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:32,955
-What about you, man?
-You know.

525
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:35,839
Just keep teaching sailing,
hang with Luke.

526
00:36:37,080 --> 00:36:40,470
His dad's dating someone new,
so that should be interesting.

527
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,954
Sounds fun.

528
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:45,954
Plus, you know, my parents are kind of
okay with this now, so it's good...

529
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:49,192
-...because I don't have to feel guilty....
-That's great, man.

530
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:51,232
Yeah, it's awesome.

531
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,714
It's awesome.

532
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:55,356
Chino, your cab's here.

533
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:57,471
All right, well...

534
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:00,197
...guess this is it.

535
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:04,437
Yeah, don't be a stranger.

536
00:37:07,240 --> 00:37:08,514
All right.

537
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,159
See you.

538
00:37:53,320 --> 00:37:55,788
-Hey, so I was thinking--
-I was thinking too.

539
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:59,954
You know, they don't even have
a water polo team here.

540
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:02,429
That's just gonna be a problem for me.

541
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:08,713
-We don't have to hug or anything?
-No.

542
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:10,757
Okay, come on in.

543
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:31,948
I kind of like eating
amongst the furniture. It's....

544
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:33,712
It's cozy.

545
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:43,078
So we leave for three months,
you tear the whole place apart.

546
00:38:43,240 --> 00:38:44,514
You're back?

547
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:47,912
There was a two-for-one special...

548
00:38:48,080 --> 00:38:50,913
-...on brooding young men.
-Are you coming back too?

549
00:38:51,600 --> 00:38:55,878
Yeah, yeah. It's a long story,
but I figure this is where I belong, so....

550
00:38:56,040 --> 00:38:57,473
Yeah.

551
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:00,432
What he said.

552
00:39:01,520 --> 00:39:04,637
Good. Because nobody leaves
this family twice.

553
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:07,628
-Welcome home.
-Thanks.

554
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:29,269
Hey. What's going on?

555
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:31,918
All right.

556
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:37,478
-So? Good to be back?
-Yeah. Yeah, it is.

557
00:39:37,640 --> 00:39:38,914
You?

558
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:43,835
My room felt so much smaller to me.

559
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:47,754
I don't know. Or perhaps I have grown
quite a bit in the last few months.

560
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:53,396
Summer had been there. She dumped
everything that reminded her of me...

561
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:56,950
-...so that should be fun come Monday.
-Y eah, Monday's gonna suck.

562
00:39:57,120 --> 00:40:00,112
Do you need anything?
Want me to...

563
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:02,635
...fire up the grill? Because, Ryan...

564
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:04,916
-...I can do that.
-No, I'm good. I'm good.

565
00:40:05,080 --> 00:40:07,548
-Tired, but good.
-Well, then.

566
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:10,837
Hey, wait, wait. How did you make
it all the way to Portland...

567
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:13,434
...from Newport in that little catamaran?

568
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:20,798
Well, Ryan, sit down, my son.
It was a long and torturous journey...

569
00:40:21,160 --> 00:40:24,118
...and I'm not gonna sugarcoat
any of the details for you.

570
00:40:24,280 --> 00:40:26,396
-Please don't.
-Because we're friends.

571
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:28,553
First...

572
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:30,914
...I sailed to Catalina.

573
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:33,876
Then I sailed to Santa Barbara.

574
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:37,430
Santa Barbara, I ran out of snacks,
freaked out a little bit...

575
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:40,797
...pawned my boat for cash,
took a Greyhound to Portland.

576
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:43,554
-T ook a bus?
-But don't say it like that. It was a local.

577
00:40:43,720 --> 00:40:47,269
Okay, have you ever been on one
of those? Not for the faint of heart.

578
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:49,476
Can't believe after all that,
you took a bus.

579
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:53,349
We should come up with a better story
for school, though. That'd be good.

580
00:40:53,520 --> 00:40:56,990
-No, no, I like the bus idea. It's cool.
-Okay, but what about maybe...?

581
00:40:57,800 --> 00:41:00,394
Boat sank, saved by whales.
It's very Whale Rider.

582
00:41:00,560 --> 00:41:01,834
What else you got?

583
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:05,515
I took the boat. The boat sank.
Saved by a mermaid.

584
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:09,919
The boat sank. Stranded on
a desert island. Volleyball....

